}

}

\subsection{Frequency summary methods}{

One or more summary methods can be specified via \verb{$frequency_summary}:\tabular{ll}{
   Value \tab Description \cr
   \code{"absolute"} \tab Absolute frequencies (default). \cr
   \code{"difference"} \tab Frequency differences (group supported vs. contradicted). \cr
   \code{"slope"} \tab Frequency slopes. \cr
}

}

\subsection{Dependencies}{

Two dependencies are registered at construction:
\itemize{
\item \strong{\code{"tree search"}} \emph{(required)} — a \link{TreeSearchCommand} defining the
search to repeat during resampling. The search is automatically cloned
and run in non-set-only mode within each replicate.
\item \strong{\code{"reference tree"}} \emph{(optional)} — a \code{ReadTreesCommand} providing a tree
on which to annotate group support frequencies calculated from the
resampling replicates.
}
}

\subsection{Command output}{

\verb{$render()} produces a string of the form
\verb{resample= \{method\} replications \{replications\} probability \{probability\} cut \{cutoff\} ...;}
with optional \verb{from 0} (when starting trees are set) and an inline tree
search specification.
}

\subsection{Queue integration}{

Calling \verb{$enqueue()} adds tree tagging commands, a
\code{UniqueTreesCommand}, and this command to a \link{CommandQueue}. Tree tagging
and plotting are inherited from \link{AbstractGroupSupportCommand}.
}

\subsection{Zero-length branch rule}{

Resampling analyses require a compatible zero-length branch rule in the
associated \link{TreeAnalysis}. The \verb{$zlb_rule} must be one of \code{"maximum"},
\code{"identical_states"}, or \code{"minimum"}. \code{\link[=set_support]{set_support()}} validates this
automatically.
}
}
